            "kind": "narrator",
            "path": "/people/narrators/19",
            "text": "أَبِي عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام )"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " قَالَ"
          }
        ]
      },
      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:51:1",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَمِيرُ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ( عليه السلام ) مَنْ تَطَبَّبَ أَوْ تَبَيْطَرَ فَلْيَأْخُذِ الْبَرَاءَةَ مِنْ وَلِيِّهِ وَ إِلَّا فَهُوَ لَهُ ضَامِنٌ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Al Nowfaly, from Al Sakuny, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said; ‘Amir Al-Momineen<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘The one who treats people (doctor) or treats animals (vet), so let him take the waiver from his guardian, or else he would be held responsible for him’."
        ]
      }
    }
